<h1>New Features</h1>
<h2>New Features</h2>
<div style="padding:0 50px;">
<ul>
	<li><b>Quicker Reservation Form:</b> The reservation form has been redesigned to make the process of making a reservation more efficient. Steps have been removed and the availability of help increased.<br/>&nbsp;</li>
	<li><b>Fixes:</b> Issues with the reservation system have been fixed. For instance, it is no longer necessary to ignore dashes in a guest's name. The two-digit year issue has also been fixed and dates now must have four-digit years.<br/>&nbsp;</li>
	<li><b>Editing:</b> You now have the ability to edit reservations. To edit a reservation, click on the 'Edit' link in the <a href="index.php">main customer screen</a>. Only the user who originally made the reservation will be able to edit it.<br/>&nbsp;</li>
	<li><b>Duplication:</b> You can now duplicate a reservation by using an existing reservation to fill in the fields. You do <b>not</b> need to be the owner of a reservation to use its information for duplication. To use this, click a reservation (or click the 'View' link next to a reservation) in the <a href="index.php">main customer screen</a> and click 'Duplicate' in the 'Actions' box at the top. The reservation form will appear with the fields already populated.<br/>&nbsp;</li>
	<li><b>More?</b> We are always looking for ideas to help improve the visitor reservations application. If you have ideas that would help us help you do your job better and more efficiently, please <a href="http://parking.arizona.edu/comments/" target="_blank">contact us</a>.</li>
</ul>

<p style="margin-left:50px;">Sincerely,<br/>PTS Staff</p>

